import{f as a}from"index-939d0dd8.js"/*tpa=https://cdn.w3cbus.com/mdui/design-1/assets/index-939d0dd8.js*/;const t={a1:"A card is a sheet of material that serves as an entry point to more detailed information.",a2:"Cards may contain a photo, text, and a link about a single subject. They may display content containing elements of varying size, such as photos with captions of variable length.",a3:"A card collection is a layout of cards on the same plane.",a4:"Usage",a5:"Cards display content composed of different elements whose size or supported actions vary.",a6:"Supported gestures",a7:"Swipe<br />Pick-up-and-move",a8:"Related components",a9:"Grid lists",a10:"For developers",a11:"Android cards",a12:"Polymer cards",a13:"Usage",a14:"Content",a15:"Behavior",a16:"Actions",a17:"Content blocks",a18:"Cards are a convenient means of displaying content composed of different elements. They’re also well-suited for showcasing elements whose size or supported actions vary, like photos with captions of variable length.",a19:"Example of a card",a20:"A card collection is coplanar, or a layout of cards on the same plane.",a21:"Example of a card collection",a22:"When to use",a23:"Use a card layout when displaying content that:",a24:"As a collection, comprises multiple data types, such as images, movies, and text",a25:"Does not require direct comparison (a user is not directly comparing images or text)",a26:"Supports content of highly variable length, such as comments",a27:"Contains interactive content, such as +1 buttons or comments",a28:"Would otherwise be in a grid list but needs to display more content to supplement the image",a29:"Cards have rounded corners.",a30:"Cards can have multiple actions.",a31:"Cards can be dismissible and rearranged.",a32:"This is a tile, not a card.",a33:"Tiles have square corners.",a34:"Tiles have no more than two actions.",a35:"A quickly scannable list, instead of cards, is an appropriate way to represent homogeneous content that doesn't have many actions.",a36:"The use of cards here distracts the user from being able to quickly scan. These list items are also not dismissable, so having them on separate cards is confusing.",a37:"Grid tiles are a clean and lightweight way to present a gallery of images.",a38:"Cards are unnecessary in a gallery of images (homogeneous content).",a39:"Cards provide context and an entry point to more robust information and views, and their content and quantity can vary greatly. Cards within a card collection can each contain a unique data set, such as a checklist with an action, a note with an action, and a note with a photo.",a40:"Don't overload cards with extraneous information or actions.",a41:"Content hierarchy",a42:"Use hierarchy within the card to direct users’ attention to the most important information. For example, place primary content at the top of the card, or use typography to emphasize primary content.",a43:"Images can reinforce other content in a card. However, their size and placement within the card depends on whether images are the primary content or are being used to supplement other content on the card.",a44:"Background images",a45:"Text is most legible when placed on a solid color background with a sufficient contrast ratio to the text. Text placed on image backgrounds should preserve text legibility.",a46:"This card collection contains cards with varied layouts.",a47:"This card collection contains cards with varied content types and layouts.",a48:"Typography can emphasize primary content.",a49:"This card collection contains cards with varied layouts and content hierarchy.",a50:"Cards have a constant width and variable height. The maximum height is limited to the height of the available space on a platform, but it can temporarily expand (for example, to display a comment field).",a51:"Cards do not flip over to reveal information on the back.",a52:"Supported gestures",a53:"Card gestures should be consistently implemented within a card collection.",a54:"Supported gestures include:",a55:"The <strong>swipe gesture</strong> may be used on a per-card basis. Limit swipe gestures within a view so that they don’t overlap with one another. For example, a swipeable card should not contain a swipeable image carousel, so that only a single action occurs when the card is swiped.",a56:"The <strong>pick-up-and-move gesture</strong> may be used if it is important for the user to be able to sort cards within a collection. But consider if filtering or sorting would better organize the content.",a57:"Card collection filtering and sorting",a58:"Card collections can be programmatically sorted or filtered by date, file size, alphabetical order, or other parameters.",a59:"The first item in the collection is positioned at the top left",a60:"The order proceeds left to right and top to bottom",a61:"Card sorting from left to right, top to bottom.",a62:"Scrolling",a63:"Card collections only scroll vertically.",a64:"Card content that exceeds the maximum card height is truncated and does not scroll, but the card can be expanded. Once expanded, the card may exceed the maximum height of the view. In this case, the card will scroll with the card collection.",a65:"Card content that exceeds the maximum card height is truncated and does not scroll",a66:"Cards may be expanded to reveal more content, without using scrolling.",a67:"On mobile, avoid placing scrollable space within a card, as it could cause two sets of scroll bars to be displayed, if one is already present.",a68:"On desktop, card content can expand and scroll internally",a69:"Card focus",a70:"When traversing through focus points on a card, all focusable elements are visited before moving to the next card.",a71:"For interfaces that depend on focus traversal for navigation (D-pad and keyboard), cards should have either a primary action or open a new view containing primary and supplemental actions.",a72:"Action selected during focus traversal",a73:"Expanded supporting text made visible, with the focus then placed on a supplemental action",a74:"The primary action in a card is typically the card itself.",a75:"Supplemental actions can vary from card to card in a collection, depending on the content type and expected outcome; for example, playing a movie versus opening a book. Within cards in a collection, position actions consistently.",a76:"Supplemental actions",a77:"Supplemental actions within the card are explicitly called out using icons, text, and UI controls, typically placed at the bottom of the card.",a78:"Limit supplemental actions to two actions, in addition to an overflow menu.",a79:"Card with action area, rich media and supporting text",a80:"Card with action areas 1 and 2, optional header, rich media, supporting text, and supplemental actions",a81:"Card with action areas 1, 2, 3 and 4, optional header, rich media, and supplemental actions",a82:"Card with action areas 1 and 2, optional header, supporting text and supplemental actions",a83:"UI controls",a84:"UI controls, like a slider, placed inline with primary content can modify the view of the primary content. For example, a slider to choose a day, stars to rate content, or a segmented button to select a date range.",a85:"This card contains UI controls within the action area block",a86:"This card contains segmented buttons within the action area block.",a87:"This card contains a slider control within the action area block.",a88:"This card contains tabs within the action area block.",a89:"Overflow menu (optional)",a90:"An overflow menu is typically placed in the upper-right corner of a card, but can be placed in the lower-right corner if doing so improves content layout and legibility.",a91:"Take care not to overload an overflow menu with too many actions.",a92:"This card contains an overflow menu in the top right.",a93:"Additional actions",a94:"Inline links within text content are strongly discouraged.",a95:"Although cards can support multiple actions, UI controls, and an overflow menu, use restraint and remember that cards are entry points to more complex and detailed information.",a96:"Use cards as an entry point to more detailed information.",a97:"Cards provide context and an entry point to more robust information and views. Don't overload cards with extraneous information or actions. Inline links within text content are strongly discouraged.",a98:"Cards can be constructed using blocks of content which include:",a99:"An optional header",a100:"A primary title",a101:"Rich media",a102:"Supporting text",a103:"Actions",a104:"These blocks can be organized to promote different types of content. For example, numbers may be emphasized by increasing their typographic scale.",a105:`On tablet/desktop, cards should follow the 24dp keyline. See <a class="do-router" href="${a("/layout/metrics-keylines.html#metrics-keylines-keylines-spacing")}">Metrics & Keylines</a> for more information.`,a106:"Primary title top padding: 24dp<br />Primary title bottom padding: 16dp<br />Action button row padding: 8dp<br />Supporting text top padding: 16dp<br />Supporting text bottom padding: 24dp",a107:"Content block types",a108:"Rich media",a109:"16:9 or 1:1 aspect ratio (recommended)",a110:"Actions",a111:"Padding: ",a112:"Primary title/text",a113:"Title: 24sp or 14sp<br />Subtitle: 14sp<br />Left and right padding: 16dp on mobile",a114:`On tablet/desktop, cards should follow the 24dp keyline. See <a class="do-router" href="${a("/layout/metrics-keylines.html#metrics-keylines-keylines-spacing")}">Metrics & Keylines</a> for more information.`,a115:"Top padding: 16dp or 24dp (when a large primary title is present)",a116:"Bottom padding: 16dp (if there are additional actions or supporting text) or 24dp (no actions or supporting text)",a117:"Supporting text",a118:"Supporting text: 14sp<br />Left and right padding: 16dp on mobile",a119:`On tablet/desktop, cards should follow the 24dp keyline. See <a class="do-router" href="${a("/layout/metrics-keylines.html#metrics-keylines-keylines-spacing")}">Metrics & Keylines</a> for more information.<br />Top padding: 16dp<br />Bottom padding: 24dp (16dp if there are additional actions or text below)`,a120:"Bullet points (but not their text), images, and buttons may extend outside of the 16dp padding.",a121:"Card collections",a122:"Card margins on mobile",a123:"Padding from edge of screen to card: 8dp<br />Space between cards: 8dp",a124:"Responsive UI",a125:"Card gutters and margins may vary on larger screen sizes, as long as they follow Material Design 8dp grid. Card margins and gutters can be 8, 16, 24, or 40dp wide.",a126:"Margins and gutters don’t need to be equal. For example, both 40dp margins and 24dp gutters can be used in the same layout.",a127:"This animation shows interactions of the following margin and gutter width variations:",a128:"margins and gutters",a129:"40dp margins and 24dp gutters",a130:"Elevation",a131:"Card resting elevation: 2dp<br />Card raised elevation: 8dp",a132:"Cards have a default elevation of 2dp.",a133:"On desktop, cards can have a resting elevation of 0dp and gain an elevation of 8dp on hover.",a134:"Card resting elevation of 2dp, and raised elevation of 8dp",a135:"On desktop, cards have a resting elevation of 0dp (left), and an elevation of 8dp on hover (right)",a136:"(desktop only)",a137:"Content block combinations",a138:"The following examples illustrate some possible combinations of content blocks.",a139:"Media area",a140:"ratio",a141:"Supporting text",a142:"Text: ",a143:"Left and right padding: ",a144:"Top padding: 16dp or 24dp (when a primary title is present)",a145:"Bottom padding: 16dp (if there are additional actions or supporting text) or 24dp (if there are no actions or supporting text)",a146:"Avatar, Title, and Subtitle area",a147:"Height: ",a148:"Top and bottom padding: ",a149:"Actions",a150:"Padding: ",a151:"Padding between actions: ",a152:"Primary text",a153:"Top padding: ",a154:"Bottom padding: ",a155:"Expanded supporting text",a156:" (Increment size based on 80dp media area)",a157:"All around padding: ",a158:"Dividers in cards",a159:"Dividers may be used to separate content areas in cards that require distinct visual separation. Dividers may also indicate seams in places where material may expand.",a160:"Content areas that can be expanded should use full-width dividers. Dividers can indicate seams in material where the material will expand when content is expanded.",a161:"This example uses a full-bleed divider. Similar to expansion of lists, this card uses a full-width divider to denote expansion.",a162:"Content areas that need more distinct visual separation should use dividers.",a163:"This example uses a full-bleed divider as a way to visually separate the slider content and list from the action below.",a164:"Use inset dividers to separate related content.",a165:"This example uses an inset divider to separate related the restaurant information from the booking section.",a166:"Material Design card for detailed information entry",a167:"Material Design card example",a168:"Material Design card collection example",a169:"Material Design card collection example",a170:"Material Design card styles",a171:"Examples of incorrect Material Design card styles",a172:"Material Design: Use lists for simple, action-light content",a173:"Material Design cards hinder quick scanning and are non-dismissable",a174:"Material Design grid tiles for a clean image gallery",a175:"Material Design: Cards are unnecessary in image galleries",a176:"Card collection with varied layouts in Material Design",a177:"Material Design card collection with varied layouts",a178:"Typography emphasizes primary content in Material Design",a179:"Material Design card collection with varied layouts",a180:"Card sorting in Material Design layout",a181:"Material Design card content truncation without scrolling",a182:"Material Design cards can expand to show more content",a183:"Material Design: Avoid scrollable space in cards on mobile",a184:"Material Design card content can expand and scroll",a185:"Material Design: Action during focus traversal",a186:"Material Design: Expanded text with a supplemental action",a187:"Material Design card with action area and media.",a188:"Material Design card with actions, media, and text",a189:"Material Design card with actions and rich media options",a190:"Material Design card with action areas and optional header",a191:"Card with UI controls in Material Design action area",a192:"Material Design card with segmented buttons in action area",a193:"Material Design card with a slider control",a194:"Material Design card with tabs in action area",a195:"Material Design card with top right overflow menu",a196:"Material Design cards for detailed information access",a197:"Material Design cards offer context, avoid overload",a198:"Material Design content blocks for organizing cards",a199:"Material Design guidelines for rich media content blocks",a200:"Material Design: Card with 2dp and 8dp elevation",a201:"Material Design: Cards with 0dp and 8dp elevation",a202:"Content block combinations in Material Design examples",a203:"Full-width divider in Material Design for expansion",a204:"Full-bleed divider in Material Design for content separation",a205:"Material Design inset divider for restaurant info and booking"};export{t as en};
